!Monday, August 11th, 2014 + prior session (whenever the dink that was)
*''PCs Present'': Amelia Dove, New & Improved Auron Kable&#8482;, Oliver Espadas
*''XP Awarded'': ~~3,860 XP (1,250 each, +110 more for Auron; 112,484 XP to date)~~ I fucked some stuff up, so everyone's XP total is now 40,000 (5k away from 10th level), meaning that total XP to date is now 123,000 XP.
**Session Attendance Award (3 @ 750 XP): 2,350 XP
**Aghek (1 @ CR 7): 1,350 XP
*''Highlights''
**Found that thirteenth kid, and he was being possessed by on of Reaver's pals from Shadow, a demon known as Aghek.
**PCs initially blew off Aghek, so he summoned allies and attacked!
**Good guys won. Aghek made a small monologue, then teleported away.
**Got back to base, learned that Ballin Stonehearth and Imlir Oakenfold died in fires suspiciously similar to those that killed the PCs' predecessors. Amelia used a //divination// for some cryptic clues.
***//Wings of darkness" .... "steel claws" .... "cloaks of flame" .... "gnashing teeth" .... "a man you once knew" .... "scales of justice" .... "speak to Morton Estavan"//
**Went to see Stormraven, learned that someone weird had been looking for them.
**Went to see Sister Deborah. Got a bit of insight into //divination// results.
**Went to see Estavan, learned more about Department-7. Estavan talked with his "old friend", the chairman of Department-7. Oliver poked in on the conversation, but couldn't track the other caller.
***''Lore Time!'' Department-7 is a private institution run by the chairman, who apparently came into this realm before Estavan did, and gave Estavan his ability to travel across planes. Judging by this ability to grant such power, it's likely the chairman can plane shift himself. Estavan and the chairman have known each other for a long time, and the chairman is basically a Wizard of Oz type guy in that he runs the whole show himself. Ms. Fellowes is merely an apparition or avatar with which this guy dispenses information. The main purpose of Estavan's business is to fund Department-7 by virtue of having a trade market that will basically never stop being viable. Both of them have considerable wealth, and the chairman hides behind a veil of secrecy to protect both his institution and himself. Department-7's goals are focused on the safety and well-being of the populace in the face of supernatural and arcane threats that this realm's society can't handle on its own.
**Sister Deborah's church was bombed. Heroes rushed to the scene!
**Auron's long lost brother was there, and bombed the place.
**Francis Kable works for Reaver and his gang, the "Brood", and sees some sort of idealistic utopia as Reaver's goal.
**~~Traitor~~ ~~Asshole~~ Francis Kable warned the heroes that if they didn't stop their meddling, more of their associates would die.
**Heroes told him to ~~kindly~~ go fuck himself. Auron was disappoint.
**Went to go see Kane d'Blade, and convinced him that the Brood was bad fucking news.
**Met with main mob boss, Louis Corsone, and talked with everyone about what to do concerning Reaver and the Brood.
**Learned that the zombies of days past were Corsone's goons, and they got caught in the crossfire, rather than being targets.
**Investigation time!
(Holy shit a lot got done this session, guys!)

